Preparations for the Queen’s Platinum Jubilee are underway and citizens in the UK are gearing up for the celebrations set to take during the four-day UK bank holiday weekend from Thursday 2 June to Sunday 5 June.  Amid all the preparations, an announcement was recently made that the lemon and swiss amaretti trifle created by Jemma Melvin is the official dessert for the Queen’s Platinum Jubilee. This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. This is a modal window. This modal can be closed by pressing the Escape key or activating the close button. The competition for this prestigious title was run by Fortnum and Mason in partnership with the Big Jubilee Lunch Charity, and applicants were required to create a pudding that was delicious, had a memorable story, and would be loved by the monarch.  Melvin’s winner pudding was inspired by the lemon posset which was served at the Queen’s wedding to Prince Philip in 1947. Here is a delicious and detailed lemon trifle recipe to recreate to celebrate the Queen’s 70th year of reign ahead of her Platinum Jubilee celebrations. For the custard For the amaretti biscuits  For the swiss rolls For the lemon curd For St Clement’s jelly For the chunky mandarin coulis  For the jewelled chocolate bark To assemle ALSO TRY: Recipe of the day: Slow cooker honey soy beef This recipe was found on independent.co.uk